      "content": "```typescript\nimport { test, expect } from '@playwright/test';\n\ntest('should successfully log in and load user profile', async ({ page }) => {\n  await page.goto('/login');\n  await page.fill('#username', 'testuser');\n  await page.fill('#password', 'password123');\n  await page.click('#loginButton');\n\n  // Stable wait for profile data by waiting for a specific element that only appears after data loads\n  await page.waitForSelector('#profileDataContainer', { state: 'visible' });\n  \n  // Asserting a known element to confirm the data is present and stable\n  await expect(page.locator('#userName')).toHaveText('Test User');\n});\n```\nThis code uses a targeted `waitForSelector` on the final data container, which is the most reliable way to ensure the asynchronous profile data has fully rendered before proceeding. The subsequent `expect` assertion confirms the presence of the expected data, guaranteeing a green checkmark for that flow.",
